Benevolent Conquerors Foundation – Static Website

A static website built with HTML, CSS, and JavaScript to showcase the mission, initiatives, and donation opportunities of the Benevolent Conquerors Foundation.

 Overview

This website serves as the digital home of our foundation. It provides:

Information about our mission and goals.

Details of our initiatives and community projects.

A simple way for visitors to support us through donations (QR code and secure payment links).

Contact details for reaching out to the foundation.

Tech Stack

Frontend: HTML, CSS, JavaScript

Hosting: GitHub Pages


Setup & Usage

Clone this repository:

git clone https://github.com/your-username/charity-website.git

Navigate to the project folder:

cd charity-website

Open the project in your browser:

start index.html 

Alternatively, drag and drop index.html into your browser.

Donations

Visitors can support the foundation by:

Scanning the donation QR code displayed on the site.

Following secure payment links provided on the Contact & Donate page.

Project Structure
charity-website/
│── index.html        # Homepage  
│── about.html        # About Us page  
│── initiatives.html  # Initiatives &Projects  
│── contact.html      # Contact &Donation page 
Images, QR codes,logos  
│── index.css/         # Stylesheets  
│── about.css/         # Stylesheets 
│──  initiatives.css/  # Stylesheets 
│── contact.css/       # Stylesheets 
│── README.ME/         # Stylesheets
│── scripts.js/        # JavaScript files  

Deploy on GitHub Pages

Push your code to a GitHub repository.

Go to Settings > Pages.

Under Source, select the branch (usually main) and root folder (/).

Save and wait for GitHub Pages to build.

Your site will be live at:

https://your-username.github.io/charity-website/

